definition.value: Discrimination against persons who are transgender.
Formal, sociotechnical, organizational systems designed to collect, process, store, and distribute information.
A place or collection containing records, documents, or other materials pertaining specifically to LGBTQIA+ persons, communities, or culture.
The state of being a biological parent.
The prevention, treatment, and management of illness or the preservation of mental and physical well-being for LGBTQIA+ persons.
Underdeveloped or otherwise smaller than average external genitalia involved in the production/maintenance of müllerian gametes or other processes involving müllerian gametes.
Underdeveloped or otherwise smaller than average external genitalia involved in the production/maintenance of wolffian gametes or other processes involving wolffian gametes.
A person who is the partner of a gay man.
A person who is the partner of a lesbian.
A person who is the partner of a bisexual woman.
A person who is the partner of a bisexual man.
A person who is the partner of a heterosexual woman.
A person who is the partner of a heterosexual man.
A person who is the partner of an asexual person.
A person who is the partner of a pansexual person.
Supernumerary clitoris.
Note that this term does not refer to a split clitoris; the word "bifid" indicates the presence of a split clitoris, not a supernumerary one.
The ritual cutting or removal of some or all of the external intersex genitalia.
A young person who is intersex.
A range of negative attitudes and feelings toward intersex persons. It has been defined as contempt, prejudice, aversion, hatred or antipathy, may be based on irrational fear and ignorance.
A business serving mostly gay men whose primary function is the serving of alcoholic beverages for consumption on the premises.
A business serving mostly lesbians whose primary function is the serving of alcoholic beverages for consumption on the premises.
The promotion of the self-affirmation, dignity, equality, and increased visibility of gay men as a social group.
The promotion of the self-affirmation, dignity, equality, and increased visibility of lesbians as a social group.
Diversities of sex characteristics, sexual orientations, sexualities, and expressions of those characteristics.
A brunch event accompanied by drag performances or during which drag performers act as waiters or as additional patrons.
A beard grown by some pre-transition transfeminine persons in denial of their transfeminine identity.
A eunuch priest of the Phrygian goddess Cybele and her consort Attis, whose worship was incorporated into the state religious practices of ancient Rome.
Sex designation classified purely, or mostly, based on an individual's apparent physical sex characteristics, particularly genitalia.

Anatomical sex can sometimes be non-specific. If external genitalia are present but not internal sex organs, for instance. More specific terms, or noting of organ presence/absence are usually more appropriate in medical contexts.
Typically, anatomical sex aligns with the concept of sex assigned at birth, although this isn't always the case, especially when considering any of various anatomical intersex conditions.

label.value: queer and transgender people of color

definition.value: Persons of color who are queer or transgender.
A person of color who identifies as queer.
A person of color who is transgender.
An interpersonal attraction which leads to the development of spiritual relationships.
Theoretical classification of sex based on differences in brain structure observations.

The idea of "brain sex" is closely related to the concept of neurosexism, the assumption that gender differences in behavior are caused by observed differences in brain structure. It has been suggested that such assumptions essentially create a self-fulfilling prophecy since male and female children are raised differently because of these assumptions.
Romantic attraction to persons of the same gender/sex.
Romantic attraction to persons of a different gender/sex.
A person's gender as represented or recognized in any of various legal systems.
A minority group whose minority status is not immediately obvious; or a minority group which is not visible (for example. "passing" of gay men as heterosexual).
A place where people engage in sexual activity with sex workers.
A brothel which offers only dolls.
A brothel attached to or otherwise related to members of the military, military units, or other military groups.

Formal or informal groups that organize sex-related activities, or establishments where patrons can engage in sex acts with other patrons. A sex club or swinger club differs from a brothel in that while sex club patrons pay an entrance fee and may pay an annual membership fee, they only have an opportunity to have sex with other patrons, not with sex workers.

A type of short-stay hotel found around the world operated primarily for the purpose of allowing guests privacy for sexual activities. The name originates from "Hotel Love" in Osaka, which was built in 1968 and had a rotating sign.

Any of various commercial venues expressly for women engaging in public sex with other women, as opposed to spaces such as parks which may be used for sexual behavior but are intended for general public use.
